  "prompt": "How can I reset password of Instagram account without email?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, if you don't have access to the email address associated with your Instagram account, the process of resetting your password becomes significantly more challenging, but not necessarily impossible.  Here's a breakdown of what you can try, ranked in order of likelihood of success:\n\n**1. Phone Number Verification (Most Likely, if you added your phone):**\n\n*   **If you linked your phone number to your account:**  When you go to the \"Forgot Password\" screen on the Instagram app, look for the option to \"Send an SMS.\"  This will send a reset code to your phone number, allowing you to create a new password. This is the most common alternative to email reset.\n\n**2. Facebook Connection (If Linked):**\n\n*   **If you linked your Instagram to your Facebook account:** Look for the \"Log In With Facebook\" option on the Instagram login screen. If your accounts are properly linked, this *should* let you access your Instagram without needing a password.  From within Instagram settings, you can then change your password.\n\n**3. Account Recovery Request with Identification (Official Method, but variable results):**\n\n*   **Through the Instagram Help Center:** This is the official, but often frustrating, method. You'll need to prove you own the account.\n\n    *   **How to Access:** On the Instagram login screen (usually on your phone), tap \"Forgot password?\"  Then, tap \"Need more help?\"  (The exact wording might vary slightly depending on your location and the Instagram app version).  Follow the prompts.\n    *   **What you'll be asked to do:**\n        *   **Provide a valid email address where Instagram can contact you.**  This doesn't have to be the original one, just one you currently have access to.\n        *   **Explain the issue:**  Clearly state that you've lost access to the original email address and need to prove ownership.\n        *   **Answer questions about your account:** Be prepared to answer detailed questions about when you created the account, who you follow, and any photos you've posted. The more information you can provide, the better.\n        *   **Submit a Selfie Video (Required for some cases):** Instagram may ask you to record a selfie video turning your head in different directions. This helps them verify that you are who you say you are. They'll provide specific instructions.\n\n    *   **What to expect:**\n        *   **Slow Response:**  Instagram's support can be very slow to respond, especially for account recovery requests.  Be patient, but follow up if you don't hear back in a reasonable amount of time (a week or so).\n        *   **Possible Rejection:**  Instagram may reject your request if they can't sufficiently verify your identity.  If this happens, carefully review their reasons and try again, providing more information if possible.\n        *   **Success is not guaranteed:** Even with all the right information, there's no guarantee that Instagram will grant you access to your account.\n\n**4. Contacting Instagram Support (Limited Effectiveness):**\n\n*   **Use the Instagram Help Center:** Navigate to the Help Center through the Instagram website. Search for articles related to account recovery.\n*   **Report Hacking (If Applicable):** If you suspect your account has been hacked and the email was changed without your permission, report it to Instagram immediately. This might expedite the recovery process.\n\n**Important Considerations and Tips:**\n\n*   **Be Honest:** Always be truthful in your communication with Instagram. Providing false information will likely result in your request being denied.\n*   **Be Persistent:** Account recovery can be a long and frustrating process. Don't give up after the first attempt, especially if you believe you have a legitimate claim to the account.\n*   **Privacy:** Be cautious about sharing personal information online. Only provide the information that Instagram specifically requests.\n*   **Security:** Once you regain access to your account, immediately change your password to a strong, unique password. Enable two-factor authentication to further protect your account from unauthorized access.\n\n**What NOT to Do:**\n\n*   **Don't use third-party password recovery services:** These services are often scams and can compromise your account security.\n*   **Don't buy followers or engagement:** This violates Instagram's terms of service and can lead to your account being suspended.\n\nIn summary, your best bet is to use your phone number if you added it to your account. If not, Account Recovery with proper ID is the next step.\n",
